Class ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.lang.RuntimeException

            • java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException

  • public class ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException
extends IndexOutOfBoundsException
    Thrown to indicate that an array has been accessed with an illegal index. The index is either negative or greater than or equal to the size of the array. Since: JDK1.0, CLDC 1.0
